dcterms:description: A benchmark task where three agents and three landmarks are generated at random locations of a 10-by-10 2D plane. The agents try to cooperatively cover all landmarks.
dcterms:title: Cooperative Navigation

dcterms:description: A benchmark task where three predators and a prey are generated at random locations of a 10-by-10 2D plane. The predators try to cooperatively catch the prey.
dcterms:title: Predator Prey

dcterms:description: A real-world task involving the routing of packets in a network, where routers are treated as autonomous agents aiming to transmit packets using minimal resources.
dcterms:title: Packet Routing Tasks

dcterms:description: A network topology used for testing scalability in packet routing tasks, representing a real-world network structure.
dcterms:title: Abilene Network
